                              (Summary of phase abstracts. After each phase this will be updated)

After Phase 1:
  Our ULTIMA 2.0 Project consists of the Scheduler and Semaphore aspects for our operating system. These components provide the operating system 
with the ability to manage processes/threads, synchronize shared resources (like the screen), and see/set the status of tasks. ULTIMA 2.0 
shows a table of the tasks that are currently active so that the user can see if a task is "running", "blocked", "ready", or "dead".
==================================================================================================================================================== |
 
After Phase 2:
  The Ultima.cpp file now shows the user 8 windows: Output window, Shared window, Thread 1 window, Thread 2 window, Thread 3 Window,
                                                    Scheduler Dump window, Semaphore Dump window, and Message Dump window.
                                                    
  The Output window is the main window that has the purpose of showing the start of the Scheduling, creation of tasks, 
  and information of what it is actively doing. 

  The Shared Window is the window that shows our semaphore working. In this window threads are trying to pass a message into it, but only
  one message may be displayed at a time. One by one, the threads will take turn writing to the shared window "Hello from thread #"

  The Thread Windows work together to pass/recieve messages. Thread 1 window will first write to the shared window, recieve messages from threads 2
  and 3, sends a message to thread 3, then ends its work. Thread 2 attempts to write to the window, gets blocked when it can't, sends a message to 
  threads 1 and 3, then tries to write to the shared window again. Thread 3 does the same as Thread 2, but also has to wait for Thread 2 to complete
  before it can write to the shared window.

  The Scheduler Dump window shows the Task ID, name, elapsed time, and status of the current tasks. In this window, Thread 2 and Thread 3
  can be seen as "BLOCKED" of "READY" when Thread 1 is running.

  The Semaphore Dump Window shows the Sema_Value indicating if the semaphore is available or in use and The Sema_Name

  The Message Dump Window shows all the messages that are passed from thread to thread.
===================================================================================================================================================== |

After Phase 3:
  Our ULTIMA Project now has memory management, IPC messaging, a Scheduler, and semaphores for resource managing. There is now an additional window 
  that shows what our MMU is doing, what is currently in Memory, which Tasks are allocated to which blocks, and which blocks are free.
  We are able to successfully allocate, write, read, and free memory with our MMU. Our project is also able to 
  detect if there is not enough RAM for a task, which will cause it to not be allocated until enough memory is available for it. 
